## ğŸ” Code Review Checklist

When reviewing CSS modules or styling changes:

- [ ] Are design tokens used instead of hardcoded values?
- [ ] Is the CSS module necessary, or could Tailwind work?
- [ ] Are class names descriptive and follow naming conventions?
- [ ] Are responsive breakpoints consistent with design system?
- [ ] Are animations accessible (respect `prefers-reduced-motion`)?
- [ ] Are tokens properly scoped (domain-specific vs global)?
- [ ] Is the CSS module file in the correct location (same dir as component)?

